1. Keep an index of generic-classes. A statement like `create Box[Integer]` should pick-up the type-realized class-definition from the index.
   If the class-definition is missing in the index, it must be created.
2. Make sure HashMap and ArrayList equivalants is supported in cljs
3. Make sure all type-declarations mandatory when the typechecker is running or while in `:typecheker on` mode.
   That means the following is invalid in typechecking mode:
      let a := 1
      let b := create Box[String]
   Only the following are valid in typechecking mode:
      let a: Integer := 1
      let b: Box[String] := create Box[String]
   Also while typechecking, all methods that return a `result` MUST declare its return type.